summary: This is an email chain between FBI agents in New York discussing the need for personnel to assist with executing a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence for digital media and computer equipment. The emails show coordination between different FBI squads, with one agent mentioning being occupied with a kidnapping case and a trial.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Mentioned as the subject whose residence is to be searched for digital media and computer equipment as part of an ongoing investigation.

keyFacts: FBI agents were planning to execute a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence for digital media and computer equipment on or around July 11, 2019.
Most of the requesting agent's squad (C-20 Crimes Against Children/Human Trafficking) was in Florida interviewing victims at the time.
The email chain shows coordination challenges between FBI squads, with one squad (C-19 Violent Crimes Task Force) being 'jammed with a trial and a couple of significant investigations.'
An FBI agent mentions catching a kidnapping case on July 9, 2019, which affected availability for the Epstein search operation.
